        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38582",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The attached blog does not mention anything which is not possible by using Zend_Translate.\r\n\r\nZend_Translate accepts to have multiple modules... see into the manual:\r\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.translate.using.html -> file structured sources.\r\n\r\nYou should simply use addTranslation() and not create a new instance when you want to add translation to an existing object.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-19T11:07:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-19T11:07:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38589",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tector",
                        "name": "tector",
                        "displayName": "Mario Gehnke",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yeah, it is possible to write an own bootstrap resource or plugin for that. The point is that a module config file setting overwrites the application config for translation if not handled by own code (This is described in the blog)\r\nSo you have the one or the other but i want it combined - and this functionality should Zend_Application_Resource_Translate provide by default (for modules).\r\nI think this would be an good improvement...",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tector",
                        "name": "tector",
                        "displayName": "Mario Gehnke",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-02-19T12:06:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-02-19T12:06:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38590",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tector",
                        "name": "tector",
                        "displayName": "Mario Gehnke",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": ".. so maybe this issue is more related to Zend_Application_Resource instead of Zend_Translate",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tector",
                        "name": "tector",
